    All Classes and Interfaces

    Classes
    Class
    Description
    App
    App.java: Bootstraps the API endpoints and backend server, using the HttpServer class built into the JDK
    Cart
    Cart: An object that represents a cart for a user.
    CartAddItemHandler
    CartAddItemHandler: An HTTP endpoint that attempts to add an item to a customer's cart, and returns the result
    CartRemoveItemHandler
    CartRemoveItemHandler: An HTTP endpoint that attempts to remove an item from a customer's cart, and returns the result
    CartSubmitOrderHandler
    CartSubmitOrderHandler: An HTTP endpoint that attempts to submit a user's order, and returns the result
    CartUpdateService
    CartUpdateService: Contains methods related to updating a user's cart
    Database
    Database.java: A class that contains static lists and hashmaps, used to represent a "database"
    GetCartHandler
    GetCartHandler: An HTTP endpoint that returns a user's cart
    GetMenuHandler
    GetMenuHandler: An HTTP endpoint that returns a restaurant's full menu
    GetOrdersHandler
    GetOrdersHandler: An HTTP endpoint that returns a restaurant's order list
    LoginHandler
    LoginHandler: An HTTP endpoint that attempts to log a user in, and returns the result
    LoginService
    LoginService: This service is in charge of handling log in requests from the user.
    MenuAddItemHandler
    MenuAddItemHandler: An HTTP endpoint that attempts to add an item to a restaurant's menu, and returns the result
    MenuEditItemHandler
    MenuEditItemHandler: An HTTP endpoint that attempts to edit a menu item and returns the result
    MenuItem
    MenuItem: An object that represents a menu item on a restaurant's menu
    MenuRemoveItemHandler
    MenuRemoveItemHandler: An HTTP endpoint that attempts to remove an item from a menu and returns the result
    MenuUpdateService
    MenuUpdateService: A service that handles functionality relating to updating a restaurant's menu
    Order
    Order: An object that represents a customer order
    RegisterHandler
    RegisterHandler: An HTTP endpoint that attempts to register a new user, and returns the result
    RegisterService
    RegisterService: This service is in charge of handling register requests from the user.
    Restaurant
    Restaurant: An object representing a restaurant
    TestGetHandler
    TestGetHandler: A template for GET request endpoints
    TestGetService
    TestGetService: A template for a service that responds to a GET request
    TestPostHandler
    TestPostHandler: A template for POST request endpoints
    TestPostService
    TestPostService: A template for a service that responds to a POST request
    User
    User: An object that represents a User
